# @Browser Mandatory Execution

When the user message includes `@Browser` (case-insensitive), you must use the browser tooling in this turn.

## Required behavior

- Treat `@Browser` as an explicit instruction to perform browser-based interaction.
- Do not skip browser actions and do not answer from assumptions or memory.
- First, call `browser_tabs` with `action: "list"` to identify existing tabs.
- If the user says "current tab", "this tab", or similar, use the active/focused tab from the tab list first.
- If a browser tab already exists, lock before interactions.
- If no tab exists, navigate first, then lock, then interact.
- Before any conclusion about page content, call `browser_snapshot` on the selected tab.
- Before clicks/types, capture a snapshot and use it to target elements.
- Never infer sheet/tab names unless they are visible in browser snapshot output.
- If browser interaction fails, report the failure and what browser steps were attempted.

## Prohibited behavior

- Do not complete `@Browser` requests without any browser tool call.
- Do not replace requested browser validation with code-only reasoning.
- Do not claim what is in the current tab without both `browser_tabs list` and `browser_snapshot` evidence.
